docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON, Aug. 14. -- Discount was a shade firmer the past week, at 1 for three months and 1/2 for short. Autumnal bills are absorbing some money, and a stronger demand for gold for the Continent has also relieved the plethora. Still the demand from every source has been insufficient to do more than stiffen rates. The continuous tall in silver causes uneasiness in financial circles.

docs.lead_paragraph: At the beginning of the week the vessels of the North Atlantic squadron are stationed as follows: The flagship Chicago is at the man-of-war anchorage in North River off West Twenty-sixth Street. The cruisers Philadelphia and Atlanta are at the Brooklyn Navy Yard. The double-turreted monitor Miantonomoh is at the same navy yard.
